modules.description: This module enables bidirectional conversion between OCaml values and YAML data structures, supporting both primitive types (integers, strings, booleans) and complex structures like records, variants, lists, and options. It provides error-aware serialization and deserialization routines to encode OCaml values into YAML format and decode YAML documents into typed OCaml representations. Typical use cases include parsing configuration files, exchanging structured data between systems, and persisting OCaml data in human-readable YAML format.

This module enables bidirectional conversion between OCaml values and YAML data, handling primitives like integers, strings, and booleans, along with complex types such as records, variants, lists, and nested structures. It supports type-safe serialization and deserialization, ensuring correct mapping between OCaml and YAML representations. Use it to read and write configuration files, exchange structured data with external systems, or implement APIs that consume or produce YAML payloads.
